1. Style FirstTest page without using Flexbox! 

Create separate CSS file where all stylings should be put. Reference to this file form <head> element. 

1.1 Style images to be standardized: 

    border: 1px solid #ddd; /* Gray border */ 

    border-radius: 4px;  /* Rounded border */ 

    padding: 5px; /* Some padding */ 

    width: 150px; /* Set a small width */ 

    height: 150px; 

1.2 Add a hover effect on image (blue shadow) 

    box-shadow: 0 0 2px 1px rgba(0, 140, 186, 0.5);   

1.3  Use semantic HTML tags <figure> and <figcaption> to wrap image and its caption 

1.4 Style <figure> element 

    vertical-align: top; 

    display: inline-block; 

1.5 Style <figcaption> as: 

    display: block; 

    font-size: 18pt; 

    font-family: cursive; 

1.6 Make a class for question text and apply style 

    text-align: center; 

    font-size: 28pt; 

    font-family: cursive; 

1.7 Add <div> element to contain all answers (<a> elements) and style it 

1.8 Make <div> to be class 'list-of-answers' and style it   

    text-align: center;  

 

2. Style SecondTest page using Flexbox to be responsive 

2.1 Put <p> elements with the image caption text to be contained by corresponding <a> element 

2.2 Add a new <div> element with class "flex-container" as container for all answers 

2.3 Style class "flex-container" 

    display: flex; 

    flex-direction: row; 

    align-items: center; 

    justify-content: space-around; 

    align-content: space-between; 

    text-align: center; 

    font-family: cursive; 

    font-size: 18pt; 

2.4.Add class "flex-item" to each <a> element and style it  

    text-decoration: none;   

2.5. Make "flex-container" to have "flex-direction: column" at 800px 

  @media (max-width: 800px) { 

    .flex-container { 

      flex-direction: column; 

    } 

  } 

 

3. Style Login page using Bootstrap to be responsive 

3.1. Add in <head> element of login.html the following Bootstrap  link and script  tags : 

<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" /> 

<link rel="stylesheet"  href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.2/css/bootstrap.min.css"> 

<script src="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.2/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script> 

3.1 Style form elements using Bootstrap CSS framework 

3.1.1 Add Bootstrap form-control class to input text fields fname and lname 

<input class="form-control" type="text id="fname" ... 

3.1.2 Replace existing login button with Bootstrap primary button: 

<input class="btn btn-primary"   

type="submit" onclick="store()" value="Login" /> 

3.2.3 Add a new Bootstrap secondary button to cancel login 

<input type="button" class="btn btn-secondary"  

value="Cancel" onclick="history.back(-1)" /> 

 

3.2. Use Bootstrap CSS framework to create a responsive grid of one row and 3 columns 

  <div class="row"> 

    <div class="col-sm-4"></div> 

    <div class="col-sm-4">Login form elements come here</div> 

    <div class="col-sm-4"></div> 

  </div> 

 

3.3.   Move elements of the login form to the second column 

 

3.4.  Add a new  <h3> element above the form with content  “Please login to your account” 

 

3.5. Add a new div elemnt to wrap <h3> and <form> elemnts and add margin 5px 

<div class="container" style="margin:5px">  
